Professor Frick is fresh, fun, and interesting. She presents material clearly and understandably, and has an obvious understanding of the material. She is a great ecologist, and her knowledge of bats is impressive.

Winifred is a great instructor and very helpful if you have any questions regarding course material. It seems the other reviewers here did not do well in the class and were upset with their grade, but rest assured Winifred is an excellent teacher and wants her students to succeed. Her research with bats is cutting edge and very interesting!

The people who wrote bad reviews for Fred must have done badly and not put much effort into this class. Her work with bats was totally interesting and inspiring.    Totally reasonable amount of work assigned and will totally help you outside of class if you ask. This is college people.

Winifred is one of the best teachers that I have had at UCSC. She is enthusiastic and experienced when it comes to ecology, conservation and biology, yet she has an approachable and accessible teaching style that makes it easy to learn a lot. She adjusts the class to the level of the students to achieve a good balance of being challenging and fun.
